<p>===</p>
<p>In this lesson I want to focus on a fast pentatonic type line I regularly play within my solos and fills.</p>
<p>Every time I use it within one of my videos I always get a heap of questions in the comments such as...</p>
<ul>
<li>What is that lick you played at... ?</li>
<li>How are you descending that fast?</li>
<li>How are you fingering it?</li>
</ul>
<p>So, I thought it'd be cool to break it down for you so you can finally see what I'm doing - and then get it into your vocabulary! ;)</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed...</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
